Selection Sort Approach:-
Find the max element and place it to the last index or do vice versa.
Take minimum element and place it to the left-most index of the array.

ALGO:
Run a loop on the array elements
Store the last index
Search for max element Index
Swap the elements with arr[maxIndex] to arr[last]
Run the loop until the array is sorted.

Solution:-
public class Main {
   public static void main(String args[]){
     int arr[]={5,1,9,2,6,-1,-56};
     SelectionSort(arr);
   } 
    public static int getMax(int arr[], int start, int end){
      int max=start;
      for(int i=start;i<=end;i++){
        if(arr[max] < arr[i]){
          max=i;
        }
      }
      return max;
    }
    public static void swapElement(int arr[], int first, int last){
      int temp=arr[first];
      arr[first]=arr[last];
      arr[last]=temp;
    }
//Function for Selection Sort
  public static void SelectionSort(int arr[]){  
    for(int i=0;i<arr.length;i++){
      int last=arr.length-i-1;
      int maxIndex=getMax(arr,0,last);// this function call will give the index of Maximum element
      swapElement(arr,maxIndex, last); // this function call will swap the array elements with arr[last] to arr[maxIndex], since we know that index of maximum element
    }
    System.out.println(Arrays.toString(arr));
  }
  
}
